works.description: A rare 1954 AJS E95 “Porcupine” motorcycle is being expected to become the world’s most expensive motorcycle when it goes on sale at the Bonham’s auction at the Pebble Beach Car Week this August. The motorcycle is one of the only four AJS E95 Porcupines built by British manufacturer AJS during World War II. The 1954 AJS E95 Porcupine, which has been with the National Motorcycle Museum in Coventry for last 20 years, got its name from its distinctive spiked fins on the sloping cylinders.
